name: Lavender
odor_profile: An aromatic floral clean note, with green, fresh spicy, licorice facets.

name: Vetiver
odor_profile: Vetivers from different parts of the world differ a lot. For example, Haitian vetiver is clean and ethereal, while the Javanese one is smoky and dusty. If we have to generalize the scent, it is earthy, woody, green.

name: Petitgrain
odor_profile: A green citrus note of leaves and crushed branches.

name: Musk
odor_profile: There is a wide variety of sources for musk smelling materials, including synthetic musks and natural ones, mainly obtained from plants, since deer musk is forbidden to obtain and sell. The musk is a secretion inside an internal pouch on the abdomen of the male deer. In order to get it, you have to kill the deer.

name: Carnation
odor_profile: A spicy floral scent, with clove-like undertone, bright and vivid.

name: Osmanthus
odor_profile: An apricot-smelling flower, soft, sensuous, with a milky, woody nd leather nuance.

name: Iris
odor_profile: A natural iris (iris root) note is earthy, woody, powdery, reminiscent of boiled carrot. A fantasy iris note is a powdery floral, reminiscent of the violet flower.

name: Immortelle
odor_profile: A sweet and dry herbaceous note, reminiscent of hay, tobacco, and honey.

name: Jasmine
odor_profile: Sweet, white floral, opulent, can be more indolic or greener and fresher when synthesized in the lab.

name: Labdanum
other_names: ladanum, ladan, ambreine, European rock rose
odor_profile: A deep, powerful, leathery and ambery note.
